rComments: Boring, rants about random bull that isn't even on the final. Looks scruffy and dirty. Pretends to be helpful and nice but is VERY rude.

try to avoid him, but if your stuck, its not the worst thing (get peter oman!). lectures were organized, but unclear, he made at least 2 mistakes on the board per class. i had no idea what was going on in lectures until i did the homework and figured it out. nice guy, funny, extra help is useful, course exam is harder than calc 1000 but still fine

stopped attending lectures in october. didn't understand a word he said in class and when i went back to review my notes, none of it made sense cause he scribbles all over the board. however he does try to be helpful when you go ask him for help.
Stopped attending his lectures 2 months ago. This teaching thing ain't working out -- I'm sure he's great at research.

Here's a tip: ALWAYS remember to bring the morning newspaper and a coffee. Then, sit in the front row and sip on your coffee and enjoy the paper. No point in listening to this guy. You'll be dumber by the end of the lecture. If you didn't sleep well last night, catch up on sleep!

Attend another lecture section if you can. Unless you enjoy gaining negative knowledge points every day... honestly, the textbook is more knowledgeable than this guy! He screws up on the board wayyy too much. He can be working a proof, screw up, and then goes off in his own little world. BOO!!!
HORRIBLE, HORRIBLE, HORRIBLE.  I'd rather sleep in and read the book than learn from him!

omg.....this guy is in his own world when he teaches, he doens't even realize that he's teaching to a class of 150+!! Seriously, the man spends so much time on tlakin bout proofs that we dont even get to do examples! Mat135 shouldn't consist this much proofs...:S
Very smart and helpful. He helps you with anything to do with math(MAT 223,237,etc.). Makes sure you understand and does his best. I hope he stays!!!
